</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugiradella.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giradella</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 10/8/00 10:43:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Anon</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/8/00 6:31:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   concerned...</span><hr size=1> this is exactly why this guild is going away.  many people from the guild and that &quot;were&quot; officers were not in attendance and now are no longer officers.  what is wrong with this picture.  how is this fair.  what did they do to lose their titles?  i personally as a former member of the guild have been curious as to what you all have been up to.  i have been keeping up with all msg board postings and also checking who in the guild is on everytime i log on.  the day i quit was when i had been on for a week at all times of the day and no one else was on.  then the few times others were on, no one said anything to me.  i was carrying on a total one side conversation.  i realize that during fights and stuff it is hard to keep up with things like that, but come on...  for an hour and a half straight?  i felt very ignored for a long time as no replys when i log on, no replys when i log off, no replys for advice from the guild...nothing.  i had a lot of fun with the guild seeing as though i was with the guild as my first one and i learned a lot through you all, but why if you are trying to keep faithful members do you ignore those that are trying to stay that way?  i would like to give huge props to those of you who helped me through everything, and for those that actually took the time with me know who this is writing right now, and for the rest of you, i am sorry that i couldnt stay to try and get to know you all better.  i tryed though, i really did.  i wish you all the best of luck in everything as i really have no bad feelings to anyone.  maybe some of you if you are trying to get some of the faithful back should look up old straying members and give them a nice tell sometime when you see them online.  coming from someone who knows, it really sucks being in a guild and feeling as left out as i did.  be good to your members, dont burn any bridges, cause one day it just might be that person you rely on to save yur arse.  we all have important jobs no matter what level, class and race.  remember that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bbenevolentorder.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=idella>Idella</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/8/00 7:33:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: concerned...</span><hr size=1> Well, I'm at a total loss as to who the &quot;anonymous&quot; person is, though I can tell they were not here from the beginning. So I, personally, would like to say a few things. After coming back from my &quot;hiatus&quot; (aka Vehement distaste for this cruel game) I saw the guild in complete disarray. There was bickering among its members almost to the point of minor civil wars. Very few of the original members were left and those who were left were having a hard time being heard anymore and were giving up hope. Now whether or not the way the guild officers was chosen was a completely right or fair way to fix things is not the point. Even in the past week I've seen the guild become closer and stronger. In fact, I haven't seen one negative comment within guild chat in awhile, outside of the stray NPC that kills so-and-so, namely me. Baka druids! So despite all that is happened I am happy to be back in the Benevolent Order and I am proud that people like Giradella and Valmar have taken the reigns that Emanie could no longer hold (due to time, not from a lack of ability of course.) So to all those still in the guild I think it's time we just forget the negative and work towards the positive. Let our faith be restored and may our bonds grow only stronger.<br>
<br>
-Idella, channeling the great Paladin Kavin and his odd way of speaking. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Anon</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/8/00 8:39:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   i agree</span><hr size=1> i agree that you would not know who i was.  you were not there when i joined, and when i left, you might have been back for 2 days...maybe.  this is where most of my problem came in.  i was not there in the beginning.  i realize that this is one of the older guilds on this server, and with this comes high level people.  so what happens with this?  all guild functions are centered around the higher level people with no reguards to the younger brothers and sisters that need help too.  there was only one time that anyone came to help me out, and that was Emanie.  i had much respect for her after this because she walked...no teleport...walked 8 zones to where i was to help me out.  other people that i asked said they were all too far away when if fact they were closer than she was.  i am not that big on power leveling, but some assistance would have been greatly appreciated in my pre-twenty levels.  but as i said before then i got to mid-twenties, where i would have been a greater asset to the guild and i still was ignored.  i think rodney dangerfield said it best &quot;i get no respect&quot;.  in the past few, i have seen a change in the guild also, a change for the better from where it was going.  this is good.  there was a time that i can remember that the guild was good.  people seemed to care about others.  i honestly hope that it gets back to this.  i do believe the thing that erked me the most was the day i hit 20.  big milestone in most peoples game.  the day i get to pick a last name.  6 people were online with me when i made the announcement of my ding to twenty and what my name was going to be.  nothing.  repeat message again.  nothing.  repeat message again.  nothing.  then i did an out of character message to the zone and out of 35 people there, 30 responded.  oh yes, i forgot to mention, 2 of the people that were on in the guild that day are now officers.  i think that this was the day that i really decided to leave the guild.  when i feel more welcome in a zone of strangers than with a guild of &quot;friends&quot; there is a problem. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugiradella.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giradella</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/8/00 10:40:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eagle.cc.ukans.edu/~stinnett/Girasmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: concerned...</span><hr size=1> To whomever this is, I am sorry if I was one of the two who were on when you hit level 20.  Had I seen that you gained the experience to earn your surname, I would have certainly congratulated you.<br>
<br>
About the officer situation.  We collectively decided that the guild needed a major reworking.  We were down to only one member who was regularly online that was an officer.  That was Khoal.  He was the <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>only</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> person who could invite people into this guild that I saw online after Tienen left us.  Occaisonally, I saw Tranitris.  I saw Baldrog once.  These were rare occaisons.  If you were one of those who lost their office, I am sorry.  The reason that the positions were re-assigned is that we cannot fully function as a guild if we have no officers who play regularly.  Surely you can understand this.  If you would step forward as a member of the guild who would like to help us rebuild, you are more than welcome to take an office.  <br>
<br>
Within the past month, much has changed in Benevolent Order.  We have lost many officers, and now, it seems that we have lost another.  I am truley sorry if we in any way offended you by reassigning positions, but it was something that had to be done if we wanted to save our guild.<br>
<br>
Addressing the level concern.  I realize that nothing was planned for the lower levels.  This was probably due to the fact that we did not have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> many</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> people that were lower than 20 at the time.  I only know of 2-3 who are presently lower than 20.  This is no excuse, I am aware of that.  Now that we have new officers, perhaps we can recruit more lower level people to join our ranks.  That is the job of Mathusis and Ndirya.  It is Khoal's job to plan events for each group of members that we have.  It is Valmar's job to make sure that these three, along with the other officers, do their jobs.  Only having 1 or 2 active officers left us in a bind.  Nobody was ever around to provide leadership.  Now, that is not the case.<br>
<br>
If you have any questions or concerns, please give me a tell in game, the next time you see that I am online.  We are not out to make any enemies or hurt any feelings.  Our goal is to build as a fully functioning group so we can help our fellow Norrathians strive for greatness. <p><hr>
