<br>
     On the points brought up by Gira and Ndirya those are truly great points and I agree with them totally. I do also agree that the officers should have meetings to discuss things and also that we are not the guild but the guild is the ppl that make it up and we should try our hardest to please those ppl and make it better for them by making decisions that would please the majority. We also need to decide how often we should have guild meetings, input on this would be greatly appreciated whether it be monthly , weekly, bi monthly or what? If we don't come up with a plan on that we may end up back where we started plus as I said in an earlier post guild meetings are ways for us to meet new members and interact with each other. It doesn't matter whether a high lvl raid is planned or not , I don't know how many times I have went to a guild meeting where all the higher lvls did something and a few ppl around my lvl showed up and we all planned a dungeon raid of our own. Don't think just because a higher lvl raid is planned that you shouldn't show up , after all if the whole guild thinks that way then only the higher lvls will show up with a few others who now have no one to grp with and nothing to do. Whereas if we all show up it will give us greater opportunity to grp together with ppl of our lvls. Don't know if that makes sense but attendance at guild meetings is something that I think is very important, goes along with more than just having that guild tag up there. Hmm well I hope I am not just rambling and some of what I am saying makes sense at least to some. I can't and won't make mandatory anything as far as rules as to how the guild acts but I will put out a simple plea for compliance to something that I feel can only help the guild in recruiting , activities planned , meeting other ppl in the guild , and just generally having fun. That is my 2cp or less and you can take that for what it is worth I am done.<br>
<br>
